	   <tr><td colspan=2>On the surface... no, I would not.<br><br>Looking a lil more into it... probably still no.<br><br>Reason is this, least for me.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ratio is king offhand.  Centi has a ratio of less than two, which is a far sight better than 2.3.  That difference in ratio would mean less damage.  Where it gets complicated is in the Skill mod.  Figure 200 slashing.  +5% 1hs would be essentially 10 extra points.  That would equate (least for me) with about 30 extra attack.  Several log parses done by Locx (sp) at the Glade indicate that every 10 Attack = 1.4% (roughly, I could be a little off on this) increase in damage.  So, if you are using a 1hs mainhand, it could perhaps be worthwile if a 5% or so increase in damage with BOTH weapons would outweigh the increased damage the better ratio of the Centi would give.  If you were using a non-1hs in mainhand, the answer to this is unequivically that it is not better than a Centi LS.  As far as if you are wielding two 1hs weapons (this being one of them), it would take a bit more parsing to figure it out, but its close enough I think I'll just stick to my Lammy/Centi.<br>&nbsp;<br>Malevant Faeshadow.&nbsp;&nbsp;Outrider.</td></tr>
